## Summary

**Created `scripts/local_vision_test.py`** — reusable Qwen3-VL vision test suite, **tested CAPTCHA detection at 70% accuracy** (80% easy, 60% hard), **discovered Qwen3-VL thinking-mode behavior** (vision requires thinking mode; /no_think returns empty), **verified image description works perfectly** (avatar test), **stored results to brain**.

Key findings:
- **Vision quality is excellent** — model correctly reads characters in its chain-of-thought
- **Main error sources**: O/0 ambiguity and response format parsing, not actual vision failures
- **Performance**: ~14.9s/image on CPU (NUC), ~144 tokens avg
- **Critical**: Qwen3-VL `/no_think` completely breaks vision output — must use thinking mode
- **CLI**: `local_vision_test.py full|quick|describe <img>|read <img>`
