**Summary of what was done:**

Created `scripts/prompt_optimizer.py` (APE/SPO-inspired prompt self-optimization loop with Thompson sampling and A/B testing), wired variant selection into `heartbeat_preflight.py` at §10.55 (selects best prompt meta-instruction combo and injects into context_brief), wired outcome recording into `heartbeat_postflight.py` at §5.05 (records prompt→outcome pairs to `data/prompt_optimization/prompt_outcomes.jsonl` and updates Beta distribution stats), tested full end-to-end loop (select→inject→record→adapt→report), verified Thompson sampling converges toward winning variants across simulated heartbeats.

**Key design decisions:**
- 3 variant dimensions (approach style, success framing, failure guard) × 3-4 variants each = combinatorial A/B space
- Thompson sampling from Beta(α,β) priors — balances exploration/exploitation naturally
- 10% epsilon-greedy exploration rate ensures all variants get tested
- Minimum 3 observations before trusting a variant's stats (falls back to defaults before that)
- Task type classification (testing/bugfix/implementation/research/etc.) for future per-type optimization
- All wiring is try/except guarded — import failure is non-fatal, zero risk to existing heartbeat pipeline
